Intel RNN (GRU) Benchmark
* test the perforamnce of tensorflow GRU on CPU and GPU
* test Intel Optimized RNN algorithm on Xeon CPU with Theano
  (tensorflow version will be available soon)

1) Instal Intel MKL (2018) & Intel Compiler
add $MKLROOT/mkl/lib/intel64 into LD_LIBRARY_PATH and LIBRARY_PATH

2) Install tensorflow:
pip install --user tensorflow

3) Install Intel Theano
git clone https://github.com/intel/theano
cd theano
python setup.py install --user

4) Change Theano configuration file
vim ~/.theanorc
copy below test into this file:
------------------------------------------------------
[global]
device = cpu
floatX = float32
cxx = icpc
mode = FAST_RUN
openmp = True
openmp_elemwise_minsize = 10
allow_gc = False
compiledir=/tmp/.theano/
#profile=True
[gcc]
cxxflags = -qopenmp -march=native -O3 -qopt-report=3 -fno-alias -qopt-prefetch=2 -fp-trap=none -g
[blas]
ldflags = -lmkl_rt
-----------------------------------------------------

5) Run test (change the size in this scripts)
./run.sh

